From Paris, John of Salisbury went to the abbey os Modtier-laCelle, where he became a clerk in the service os the Abbat Petrus Cel· lensis, to whom he afterwards addressed some lettersss. After staying there about three years, he returned to England and entered

the household of Theobald, Archbishop of Canterbury. Alter the death of this Prelate‚ John of Salisbury remained with his successor, the celebrated Thomas a Becket. From this time to the martyrdom of his patron, John adhered with unflinching fidelity to the cause which he had espoused, and was the first os the Archbishop's friends who was exiled in their masters behalf.
